 Uitenhage - Kwanobuhle police and detectives from the Operational Command Centre in Uitenhage have launched a search for suspects involved in a house robbery that occurred at about 00:45 on Friday morning. According to police spokesprson, Captain Gerda Swart, the house robbery happened along Dlala Street, Kwanobuhle. "It is alleged that two suspects (one had a firearm) entered the residence of the 52-year-old female and demanded cash," she described. "The suspects took cash, a Plasma TV, laptops and cellphones and fled the scene in a Nissan np200 bakkie. "No one was injured during the robbery and the victim notified the police." Capt Swart said that Uitenhage police recovered the bakkie soon afterwards, that was allegedly used during the commission of the house robbery. "It was found abandoned next to the road in the Rooihoogte area, Uitenhage, at about 01:30," she added. "The suspects already fled and the vehicle was handed in to be processed by our Forensic experts. Detectives are investigating a case of house robbery. "Anyone with information about the suspects can contact Detective Warrant Officer Wouter Verwey on 0848462273 or SAPS Kwanobuhle on 041 9788600." Capt Swart said that the South African Police Service is encouraging the community to assist with the fight against crime by phoning Crime Stop 08600 10111 or Crime Line SMS 32211 with their tips. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 